Description: Provides exact finite-sample inferential procedures for
    singly and multiply released plug-in sampling (PS) synthetic datasets
    under a multivariate normal model, extending the single-release
    framework of Klein, Moura and Sinha (2021)
    <doi:10.1007/s13571-019-00215-9> to M >= 1 synthetic releases.
    The key insight is that M independently released PS synthetic datasets
    of size n may be stacked into a single dataset of size Mn, yielding
    exact pivotal procedures for four features of the covariance structure:
    generalised variance, sphericity, independence between variable subsets,
    and regression coefficients. All procedures reduce to the single-release
    case when M = 1. Includes S3 classes with print, summary, and plot
    methods; multivariate normality assessment; comparison with naive
    asymptotic benchmarks; and a comprehensive vignette with a real-data
    illustration using Brittany soil survey data (Morvan et al., 2023).
